Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/annotatedBy
Object: Relates an annotation to a agent.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/hasConcept
Object: Relates an annotation to a concept.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/Annotation
Object: A relationship between an annotatable thing and a concept or free-text tag. e.g. an act of subject indexing.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/uncontrolledTag
Object: To allow for annotations that reference free text tags rather than controlled concepts.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/annotatedAt
Object: Date time an annotation was created.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/Concept
Object: A concept. Similar to a SKOS concept / a library subject term.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/indexerNote
Object: A note for indexers. Provides additional guidance on use of the concept.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/AnnotatableThing
Object: A thing which can be annotated with a concept or free text tag. e.g. a debate or petition or answer.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/hasBroaderConcept
Object: Relates a concept to a broader concept.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/historyNote
Object: A history note. Textual description of editorial changes to a concept over time.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/hasAnnotation
Object: Relates an annotatable thing to an annotation.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/ConceptScheme
Object: A concept scheme. Provides an arbitrary way to group concepts e.g. Commons Library to Lords Library.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/
Object: Concept ontology for UK Parliament. Deprecated in favour of SKOS.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/Agent
Object: A person or group. In this context a librarian or machine subject indexing annotatable things.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/scopeNote
Object: A scope note. Textual description of the intended usage of a concept.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/inConceptScheme
Object: Relates a concept to a concept scheme.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/hasRelatedConcept
Object: Relates a concept to another concept.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/concept/hasFocus
Object: Relates a concept to a real world thing that is its focus e.g. The concept / library subject term Winston Churchill to the person Winston Churchill.
